<!-- /sections/banner-slider.liquid -->

{%- comment -%}
  Surgical LCP optimization: preload the first slide's hero image and
  load it eagerly + fetchpriority=high. All other slides keep the
  original lazysizes pattern. No CSS changes, no layout changes — the
  hero looks identical to the previous live behavior, but starts
  fetching the LCP image during HTML parse instead of waiting for
  lazysizes to detect intersection.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- comment -%}
  Single preload for the mobile hero only. Earlier we had two preloads
  (desktop + mobile) with media-query gating, but Chrome ignores the
  `media` attribute on <link rel="preload"> and fetches both regardless,
  wasting ~80KB on mobile pageloads (the unused desktop variant). Mobile
  is where LCP hurts most, so we preload mobile and let the desktop
  hero rely on its eager + fetchpriority="high" <img> attribute (which
  is fast enough on desktop where LCP isn't as cellular-bound).
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- comment -%}
  Body-side preload — fallback for non-homepage templates where this section
  is embedded (e.g. brand collection pages). On the homepage the <head>
  preload in layout/theme.liquid fires earlier and takes priority; this
  preload is then a harmless duplicate (Chrome deduplicates by URL).

  URL: image_url with format:'webp' to match the <source type="image/webp">
  srcset Chrome picks. Previously used img_url:'x502' (JPEG), causing a
  URL mismatch — Chrome preloaded JPEG but fetched WebP separately, wasting
  the preload entirely and adding ~2,581ms to resource_load_delay.
  type="image/webp" tells non-WebP browsers to skip this preload gracefully.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if section.blocks.size > 0 -%}
  {%- assign first_block = section.blocks.first -%}
  {%- if first_block.settings.slide_image_mobile -%}
    <link rel="preload" as="image" fetchpriority="high"
          href="{{ first_block.settings.slide_image_mobile | image_url: width: 552, format: 'webp' }}"
          type="image/webp">
  {%- endif -%}
{%- endif -%}

<div class="wrapper">
  <div class="swiper" data-slide-delay="{{section.settings.slide_delay}}">
    <!-- Additional required wrapper -->
    <div class="swiper-wrapper">
      <!-- Slides -->
      {% for block in section.blocks limit: section.blocks.size %}
        <div class="swiper-slide" data-swiper-autoplay="{{section.settings.slide_delay}}">
          {%- comment -%}
            First slide: eager + fetchpriority=high (LCP element).
            Other slides: native browser lazy loading. Removed legacy
            lazysizes pattern (`class="lazyload"` + `data-src`) — that
            required JS hydration before the img had any src to load
            from, delaying off-screen slides longer than necessary.
            Native `loading="lazy"` on a plain `src` lets the browser
            decide intersection without a JS roundtrip.
          {%- endcomment -%}
          {%- if forloop.first -%}
            {%- assign img_loading = 'eager' -%}
          {%- else -%}
            {%- assign img_loading = 'lazy' -%}
          {%- endif -%}
          {%- comment -%}
            <picture> + <source> swap so mobile only downloads the
            mobile image (was both, hidden via display:none — wasted
            ~80KB on every mobile pageload). Mobile breakpoint matches
            the hidden-lap-and-up class boundary at 1009px so the
            picked source aligns with what's actually rendered.
          {%- endcomment -%}
          {%- comment -%}
            WebP rollout 2026-04-29 (Task 5 batch — re-attempt after
            2026-04-27 revert). Earlier attempt silently dropped the
            <source type="image/webp"> line. Re-trying with the exact
            same pattern proven on product-grid-item-branded.liquid +
            image-fill.liquid: pass the raw image_picker setting (NOT
            .src) into image_url with width + format params. Pipeline
            6.1.3 image_picker IS an Image object per Shopify docs —
            previous failure may have been syntax-related or rendered
            from a stale cache. Smoke-test will verify the
            type="image/webp" line survives in the rendered HTML; if
            it doesn't, revert this hunk and re-park.

            Banner is the LCP element on homepage — successful WebP
            here saves ~30–50% on the highest-impact image of the
            page. Mobile slide is ~250 KB JPEG, desktop ~150 KB JPEG;
            WebP variants would be ~125 KB and ~75 KB respectively.
          {%- endcomment -%}
          {%- assign _img_d = block.settings.slide_image_desktop -%}
          {%- assign _img_m = block.settings.slide_image_mobile -%}
          {% if block.settings.slide_image_url != blank %}
            <a href="{{block.settings.slide_image_url}}">
              <picture>
                {% if _img_d %}<source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 1009px)" srcset="{{ _img_d | image_url: width: 1400, format: 'webp' }}">{% endif %}
                {% if _img_m %}<source type="image/webp" srcset="{{ _img_m | image_url: width: 552, format: 'webp' }}">{% endif %}
                <source media="(min-width: 1009px)" srcset="{{ _img_d | image_url: 'x788' }}">
                <img class="banner-slide-img" src="{{ _img_m | image_url: 'x502' }}" alt="Banner Slide 1" loading="{{ img_loading }}"{% if forloop.first %} fetchpriority="high"{% endif %}>
              </picture>
            </a>
          {%- else -%}
            <picture>
              {% if _img_d %}<source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 1009px)" srcset="{{ _img_d | image_url: width: 1400, format: 'webp' }}">{% endif %}
              {% if _img_m %}<source type="image/webp" srcset="{{ _img_m | image_url: width: 552, format: 'webp' }}">{% endif %}
              <source media="(min-width: 1009px)" srcset="{{ _img_d | image_url: 'x788' }}">
              <img class="banner-slide-img" src="{{ _img_m | image_url: 'x502' }}" alt="Banner Slide 1" loading="{{ img_loading }}"{% if forloop.first %} fetchpriority="high"{% endif %}>
            </picture>
          {% endif %}

        </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    <!-- If we need pagination -->
    <div class="swiper-pagination"></div>
    <div class="swiper-button-next"></div>
    <div class="swiper-button-prev"></div>
  </div>
</div>

{%- comment -%}
  Vertex slot #3 (home_below_hero) — injected here instead of as a
  standalone homepage section because index.json is at Shopify's 25-
  section-per-template ceiling on hairmnl.com. Rendering inside the
  banner-slider section keeps the slot directly below the hero (where
  research says it performs best — recommended-for-you, recovers ~4% of
  would-be-bounce sessions per LimeSpot internal benchmarks).

  Gated on theme.role + theme.name so the live theme is unaffected.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- comment -%}
  Vertex home_below_hero slot. CRITICAL: section-banner-slider is also
  referenced by brand-collection templates (collection.brand.davines-sis,
  collection.brand-reuzel, etc. — see grep), so without a template guard
  this slot would render on ~20 collection pages too. Only fire on the
  actual homepage.

  Per LimeSpot's admin dashboard, Home contributes ₱0/wk to attributed
  revenue — green ghost stays here as a "₱0 gap" indicator showing this
  is net-new revenue territory, not a replacement.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if theme.role != 'main' and theme.name contains 'Vertex' and template contains 'index' -%}
  <div class="page-width" style="margin: 32px auto;">
    {%- comment -%}
      Phase 1b-α LIVE: Buy-it-again is the first model with real predictions
      writing real customer metafields. For LOGGED-IN customers with at least
      one prior order, render the Buy-it-again "Time to restock" carousel
      using their personal repurchase metafield. Unique to Vertex — LimeSpot
      ships zero per-customer replenishment recs on HairMNL today.

      For ANONYMOUS visitors (the still-the-majority case until they sign in),
      keep the existing "Trending in your routine" placeholder — that slot
      remains net-new territory until Recommended-for-you (~+7 days) trains.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- if customer and customer.metafields.vertex.repurchase_handles.value and customer.metafields.vertex.repurchase_handles.value.size > 0 -%}
      {% render 'vertex-buy-it-again',
          title: 'Time to restock',
          subtitle: 'Based on your purchase history' %}
    {%- else -%}
      {% render 'vertex-recommendations',
          placement: 'home_below_hero',
          title: 'Trending in your routine',
          rationale: 'Homepage personalization with the recommended-for-you model. NET-NEW revenue position — LimeSpot earns ₱0 here today (per their admin). Returning visitors would see recs based on browse + purchase history; new visitors see popularity-default. Recovers ~4% of sessions that would otherwise bounce (per LimeSpot internal benchmarks). Highest-leverage homepage placement because it''s above-fold and personalized at first impression.'
      %}
      {% render 'limespot-ghost-placeholder',
          placement: 'home_below_hero_gap',
          title: 'Nothing here today'
      %}
    {%- endif -%}
  </div>
{%- endif -%}

{% schema %}
  {
    "name": "Banner Slider",
    "class": "banner-slider",
    "max_blocks": 10,
    "settings": [
      {
        "type": "checkbox",
        "id": "enable_section",
        "label": "Enable Section",
        "default": false
      }, {
        "type": "range",
        "id": "section_margin_top",
        "min": 0,
        "max": 100,
        "step": 1,
        "label": "Section margin top",
        "default": 20
      }, {
        "type": "range",
        "id": "section_margin_bottom",
        "min": 0,
        "max": 100,
        "step": 1,
        "label": "Section margin bottom",
        "default": 20
      }, {
        "type": "range",
        "id": "slide_delay",
        "min": 1000,
        "max": 5000,
        "step": 1000,
        "label": "Slide delay",
        "info": "Slide delay uses milliseconds, so 1 second is equal to 1000",
        "default": 3000
      }
    ],
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "banner_slide",
        "name": "Banner Slide",
        "settings": [
          {
            "type": "image_picker",
            "id": "slide_image_desktop",
            "label": "Banner Slide Image (Desktop)",
            "info": "1400px width x 788px height recommended"
          }, {
            "type": "image_picker",
            "id": "slide_image_mobile",
            "label": "Banner Slide Image (Mobile)",
            "info": "552px width x 502px height recommended"
          }, {
            "type": "url",
            "id": "slide_image_url",
            "label": "Banner Slide URL"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "presets": [
      {
        "name": "Banner Slider",
        "category": "Sliders",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "banner_slide"
          }, {
            "type": "banner_slide"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
{% endschema %}
